{
  "text": "Step 6 is a fast greedy enumeration method introduced by Huang et al. [CITATION_1] . Adjacent symmetric classes in each group are swapped and flipped. Totally 8 transformations are considered ( , , , , , , , ) if the group is balanced. Otherwise only two transformations are considered ( , ) . The transformation leading to the smallest truth table is chosen. This procedure is repeated until no improvement produced. This step generates a semicanonical form.",
